Step 1: Project Overview



Tools:  Jupyter Notebook, Spyder

Programming Language:  Python

Data Science Libraries: Pandas, Sci-kit Learn, Matplotlib, Seaborn

Data Sources: UCI Machine Learning Repository

Domain: Banking and Finance

Abstract:  It is important for a bank to know whether its credit card client under goes default or not. One can predict the defaulters on way before they go default using the machine learning models.

Having the history of the bill repayments of credit card clients, one can develop a machine learning model to predict the probability of them going default.

Nave Bayes classifier is used here to predict the default status of credit card clients.
